Rating: 4
Excellent, very versatile recipe for basic popovers. It's foolproof, so long as you do not open the oven during cooking! The cooking time seems to vary dramatically with location, so I keep my eye on them. In my own home, after the first 20 minutes at 450, they are almost done. Another 5 min at 350 and they're perfect. Sometimes I sprinkle fresh parmesan or crumble blue cheese on top, right before baking. These make for a great impromptu replacement to dinner rolls, and are great for a breakfast on the go. They are super quick to whip up and make minimal mess. This recipe is very adaptable to a variety of uses. When I am doing a sweet version of these, I add just the smallest amount of vanilla bean paste to the milk. I have noticed they do rise quicker when my ingredients are at room temperature. Batter should be quite runny, not thick.

