Rating: 4
This is a very good recipe for basic popovers. I have made them many times and have found some things that make a difference in the outcome. Allow all the ingredients to reach room temperature. Do not substitute low fat or skim milk for whole milk. Give the batter a brief but vigorous whisk before putting the batter in the cups. Incorporating air into the batter helps them rise.DO NOT OPEN THE OVEN DOOR DURING BAKING! Have faith that they'll "POP". We serve these at tea with butter and strawberry preserves, just like the Jordan Pond House at Acadia National Park!

