Rating: 4
For those of you whose popovers shrink when they come out. The inside is not done enough. If you think they are too dark, cook them at 450 for 15 minutes and then reduce to 350 for another 18 - 20 minutes. One other suggestion from Americas Test Kitchen Cookbook. The popovers will be even taller if you let the batter rest for 30 minutes before pouring in a hot pan. This recipe is correct. Hot oven, Hot Pan and baking times.

