This is a pretty good popover recipe - I use it often as I have yet to find the perfect, better one. I don't have a popover tin so I use a non-stick muffin tin instead, and simply reduce the cooking time to 10-15 min @450 and 15 min @375 in order to accomodate the smaller size. I've never had a problem with them not popping, but I will warn you that you *must* either sift the flour or break it up very thoroughly with a whisk or fork, and every time I've not buttered the pan the popovers have stuck to the cups very badly. Overall, a very solid recipe. Adding a little bit of melted butter to the batter doesn't seem to affect the 'pop', but it definitely makes them more indulgent!

